parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS system can cause the brakes to malfunction, leading to increased stopping distances, loss of control, and accidents, which can result in serious injury or death.
symptoms: The ABS system fails to engage
the brakes become stiff or unresponsive
the rear brake pedal locks up or becomes inoperable
the front brake lever freezes
the brakes release and then re-engage
the vehicle experiences increased stopping distances.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear brake pedal can cause the loss of braking power, leading to accidents or loss of control, which can result in serious injury or death.
symptoms: The rear brake pedal becomes stuck or inoperable
the rear brake pedal has no effect on the vehicle's stopping power
the rear brake pedal seizes up without warning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front brake lever can cause the loss of braking power, leading to accidents or loss of control, which can result in serious injury or death.
symptoms: The front brake lever becomes stiff or unresponsive
the front brake lever freezes
the front brake lever has no effect on the vehicle's stopping power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty fuel sensor can cause the fuel gauge to malfunction, leading to sudden and unexpected fuel depletion, which can result in engine damage, rapid deceleration, and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The fuel gauge drops suddenly and without warning
the fuel sensor fails repeatedly
the fuel gauge is intermittent
the fuel gauge does not provide accurate readings.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Inaccurate fuel gauge readings can cause drivers to run out of fuel unexpectedly, leading to engine damage, rapid deceleration, and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The fuel gauge drops suddenly and without warning
the fuel gauge is intermittent
the fuel gauge does not provide accurate readings
the fuel gauge fails to provide a warning before running out of fuel.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Design Issue with Fuel Sensor Configuration
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A design issue with the fuel sensor configuration can lead to repeated failures, causing drivers to experience sudden and unexpected fuel depletion, which can result in engine damage, rapid deceleration, and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The fuel sensor fails repeatedly
the fuel sensor has a different configuration than the original
the fuel sensor does not provide accurate readings.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Shifter and Left Foot Pedal Mounting Bolt Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the bolt that holds the shifter and left foot pedal can cause the pedal to rotate down and become unusable, leading to loss of control and potential accidents, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: The left foot pedal breaks loose and rotates down
the pedal becomes unusable
the pedal falls to the pavement
difficulty shifting gears
loss of control while driving.
